WEBVTT

00:02.003 --> 00:03.493
Previously on Lost:

00:03.921 --> 00:07.664
They come, they fight, they destroy,

00:07.758 --> 00:10.795
they corrupt. It always ends the same.

00:11.846 --> 00:16.806
But it only ends once. Anything that
happens before that is just progress.

00:16.893 --> 00:19.100
I'm not gonna kill Jacob, Ben.

00:20.438 --> 00:21.518
You are.

00:21.606 --> 00:23.016
Do what I asked you to, Ben.

00:23.107 --> 00:24.893
I want you to understand one thing.

00:26.110 --> 00:27.691
You have a choice.

00:30.573 --> 00:32.154
They're coming.

00:37.914 --> 00:41.702
The Dharma folks at the Swan worksite,
they're gonna dri|| into the ground

00:41.792 --> 00:44.329
and accidentally tap into
a massive pocket of energy.

00:44.420 --> 00:48.834
I think I can negate that energy.
I'm gonna detonate a hydrogen bomb.

00:48.925 --> 00:52.008
If we can do what Faraday said,
our plane never crashes.

00:52.094 --> 00:54.176
Flight 815 lands in Los Angeles.

00:56.599 --> 00:58.260
Hurry up, doc!
What are you waiting for?

01:09.779 --> 01:11.144
We hit the pocket!

01:18.120 --> 01:19.826
- Juliet!
- No!

01:21.499 --> 01:23.831
lgotyou.
No,dontletgo!

01:24.919 --> 01:26.659
Juliet! No!

01:33.678 --> 01:35.384
Come on!

01:38.683 --> 01:42.346
Come on! Come on, you son of a bitch!

02:19.181 --> 02:20.512
So how's the drink?

02:23.936 --> 02:27.474
- It's good.
- That's not a very strong reaction.

02:27.565 --> 02:30.648
Well, it's...
It's not a very strong drink.

02:34.071 --> 02:36.778
- Don't tell anyone.
- It'll be our secret.

02:47.460 --> 02:51.203
Ladies and gentlemen, the captain has
turned on the "fasten seat belts" sign.

02:51.297 --> 02:54.039
- Please return to your seats.
- It's normal.

02:54.133 --> 02:57.341
My husband said the planes
want to stay in the air.

03:00.097 --> 03:01.257
Sounds like a smart man.

03:01.349 --> 03:04.967
You be sure and tell him that
when he gets back from the bathroom.

03:05.061 --> 03:07.552
Well, I'll keep you company
until he does.

03:07.646 --> 03:09.182
Don't worry, it'll be...

03:29.794 --> 03:31.625
You can let go now.

03:35.633 --> 03:38.124
It's OK. You can let go.

03:47.228 --> 03:51.847
- Looks like we made it.
- Yeah. We sure did.

03:51.941 --> 03:55.559
Sorry about the unexpected bumps, folks.
We just hit a pocket of rough air.

03:55.653 --> 03:57.518
It should be a smooth ride
from here on out.

03:57.613 --> 03:59.979
Remind me to hold it next time, will ya?

04:03.994 --> 04:06.406
I almost died in that bathroom.

04:06.497 --> 04:09.614
Now I know how the laundry feels
when it's in the dryer.

04:13.045 --> 04:16.663
- I missed you.
- I missed you, too, beautiful.

05:04.013 --> 05:07.301
- Excuse me.
- I'm sorry, mate. Is this your seat?

05:07.391 --> 05:09.848
- The stewardess said it was empty.
- No, I'm at the window.

05:09.935 --> 05:10.924
Oh, right.

05:17.526 --> 05:18.982
Do you mind if! sit here?

05:19.069 --> 05:21.936
The fella next to me has been
snoring since we took off from Sydney.

05:23.449 --> 05:25.531
- Yeah, no problem.
- Thanks, brother.

05:38.631 --> 05:40.747
- Something wrong?
- No, you just...

05:41.425 --> 05:42.835
Do I know you from somewhere?

05:45.930 --> 05:47.420
Well, I'm not sure.

05:50.059 --> 05:52.596
- Desmond.
- Jack.

05:52.686 --> 05:54.472
Nice to meet you, Jack.

05:54.980 --> 05:56.265
Or to see you again.

07:38.792 --> 07:44.788
Juliet! I got you.
No! No, don't let go!

07:45.549 --> 07:48.086
Juliet! No!

07:48.802 --> 07:52.715
Come on. Come on, you son of a bitch!

08:43.107 --> 08:44.688
Hey!

09:17.683 --> 09:19.173
Hello?

09:25.983 --> 09:27.143
Hello?!

09:39.329 --> 09:40.489
Hey!

09:41.248 --> 09:45.036
Hey! Hey! Kate!
It's OK. It's me, Miles. It's OK.

09:48.589 --> 09:50.250
- What happened?
- What?

09:50.340 --> 09:51.921
Where are we?

09:52.009 --> 09:54.500
I can't... I can't hear you.
Are your ears ringing?

09:58.640 --> 10:00.050
What is it?

10:05.147 --> 10:07.388
- We're back.
- Back where?

10:19.995 --> 10:21.075
No.

10:22.664 --> 10:24.200
Is that the construction site?

10:25.542 --> 10:27.999
No. That's the Swan hatch...

10:29.004 --> 10:30.790
...after Desmond blew it up.

10:32.174 --> 10:34.210
Guess we're not in 1977.

10:45.646 --> 10:47.932
Jack? Jack.

10:51.235 --> 10:53.226
Can you hear me? Jack!

10:55.948 --> 10:57.108
What happened?

10:59.076 --> 11:01.818
- Where are we?
- At the hatch.

11:15.217 --> 11:19.460
- What? They built it?
- Yeah. They built it.

11:22.933 --> 11:24.093
Sawyer!

11:27.771 --> 11:28.851
You were wrong!

11:30.107 --> 11:32.143
That's the damn Swan hatch!

11:32.734 --> 11:37.398
Blown up, just like we left it,
before we started jumping through time!

11:38.448 --> 11:40.825
You said we could stop it
from ever being built!

11:40.909 --> 11:43.321
That our plane would never
crash on this island!

11:43.412 --> 11:46.324
- Stop it! Stop it!
- This ain't LAX!

11:46.415 --> 11:48.701
You blew us right back
where we started!

11:50.252 --> 11:51.287
Except Juliet's dead.

11:54.006 --> 11:56.543
She's dead, you son of a bitch,
'cause you were wrong.

11:58.468 --> 12:00.004
Sawyer...

12:01.972 --> 12:03.553
...l'm sorry.

12:04.224 --> 12:06.135
I thought we were supposed to...

12:08.103 --> 12:10.469
- I thought it would work.
- Well, it didn't!

12:24.912 --> 12:28.700
- You in line?
- No, l'mjust waiting for my friend.

12:31.335 --> 12:35.078
- I'm sorry. I didn't see you there.
- It's OK. It's OK.

12:35.172 --> 12:37.083
Best get back to our seats, sweetheart.

12:47.517 --> 12:49.018
Lasagna.

12:51.521 --> 12:54.763
No. No knife and fork for you, honey.

12:54.858 --> 12:58.191
What do you think I'm gonna do,
stab you and run?

13:00.030 --> 13:01.895
Hey, watch where you're going, buddy.

13:05.077 --> 13:07.614
Sorry. My bad.

13:10.207 --> 13:12.789
Say it. Come on, please? Just once.

13:12.876 --> 13:15.959
- I really don't want to, dude.
- I love those commercials.

13:16.046 --> 13:19.209
Come on, just do the Australian accent,
and I'll leave you alone.

13:19.716 --> 13:21.547
All right. Fine. All right.

13:23.428 --> 13:25.214
Have a cluckity-cluck day, mate!

13:28.225 --> 13:29.214
That's...

13:30.894 --> 13:32.350
You know who this is?

13:32.437 --> 13:34.849
This is the owner
of Mr. Cluck's Chicken.

13:34.940 --> 13:37.852
And he's back here
riding coach with the rest of us yutzes!

13:39.069 --> 13:42.311
- How about that?
- Hey... Do you mind me asking,

13:42.406 --> 13:46.399
how exactly did a guy like you
get to own a major corporation?

13:46.493 --> 13:50.281
I won the lottery
and I like chicken, so I bought it.

13:52.582 --> 13:55.073
Good. Good for you.

13:58.422 --> 14:01.630
You know, you really shouldn't
tell people you won the lottery.

14:01.717 --> 14:02.752
Yeah? Why not?

14:02.843 --> 14:05.425
'Cause they'll take advantage of you.
That's why not.

14:08.348 --> 14:10.509
Thanks for the advice,
but it's not gonna happen.

14:10.600 --> 14:11.976
It's not?

14:12.060 --> 14:15.177
Nope. Nothing bad ever happens to me.

14:16.440 --> 14:18.351
I'm the luckiest guy alive.

14:30.454 --> 14:33.196
- Whatjust happened?
- I found a flashlight.

14:33.290 --> 14:35.451
Dude, who cares?
The sky just went from day to night.

14:35.542 --> 14:38.204
- What happened?!
- I think we moved through time.

14:39.963 --> 14:41.043
How do you know that?

14:41.131 --> 14:44.373
White flash. Headache. Can't hear.

14:44.468 --> 14:47.084
- Happened to me before.
- What about Jack and everyone else?

14:47.179 --> 14:48.760
- They move through time, too?
- I don't know.

14:48.847 --> 14:51.213
They took one of the vans
and went up to the worksite.

14:51.308 --> 14:54.220
And then I heard gunfire.

14:54.311 --> 14:57.269
- ...back to this island!
- You hear that, dude?

14:57.355 --> 14:59.892
- lt's Sawyer.
- Stay here with Sayid.

14:59.983 --> 15:03.896
If you've got an explanation, Jack,
I'm waiting to hear it!

15:03.987 --> 15:05.898
The bomb must've gone off.

15:05.989 --> 15:08.822
Think if the atom bomb went off,
we'd still be standing here?!

15:09.409 --> 15:11.786
- I don't know.
- That's right! You don't!

15:11.870 --> 15:14.577
- For once, you don't know!
- Jack!

15:16.374 --> 15:18.660
- Sayid needs help.
- Where is he?

15:18.752 --> 15:21.243
With Hurley at the van.
Two minutes away.

15:21.338 --> 15:23.545
He's still bleeding.
We don't know what to do.

15:26.093 --> 15:27.583
Help me.

15:30.263 --> 15:33.255
What do you say, Doc?
Got another great idea to save Sayid?

15:33.350 --> 15:35.807
- Maybe there's a nuke laying around.
- Hey, shut up!

15:41.525 --> 15:42.731
Help!

15:47.864 --> 15:48.899
Juliet!

15:50.033 --> 15:51.898
- James?
- Oh, my God.

15:53.036 --> 15:54.401
Juliet!

15:59.000 --> 16:00.956
Oh, God. Oh, God, this is gross.

16:06.216 --> 16:09.504
Don't worry, dude.
Everything's gonna be fine.

16:12.681 --> 16:14.046
When I die...

16:16.726 --> 16:19.513
...what do you think will happen to me?

16:20.814 --> 16:22.224
Just try not to talk, dude.

16:23.024 --> 16:25.481
l've tortured more people
than I can remember.

16:27.028 --> 16:28.814
l've murdered.

16:28.905 --> 16:30.896
Wherever I'm going...

16:32.576 --> 16:34.487
...it can't be very pleasant.

16:34.578 --> 16:37.240
- Sayid, come on.
- I deserve it.

16:43.253 --> 16:44.743
Hello?

16:47.757 --> 16:49.008
Jin?

16:55.098 --> 16:56.087
Jin!

17:00.562 --> 17:02.098
l've gota gun!

17:02.189 --> 17:03.975
And I know how to shoot it!

17:32.093 --> 17:33.503
Hello, Hugo.

17:35.305 --> 17:36.670
You got a minute?

18:14.177 --> 18:15.713
You're wasting your time, man.

18:18.014 --> 18:19.754
This plane goes down
in the ocean out here,

18:19.849 --> 18:22.682
I think our chances of survival
are exactly zero.

18:24.312 --> 18:28.271
Actually, in calm seas
with a good pilot,

18:28.358 --> 18:30.269
we could survive a water landing.

18:30.360 --> 18:32.646
And the fuel tanks are buoyant enough

18:32.737 --> 18:35.114
to keep us afloat
until we got in the life rafts.

18:37.033 --> 18:39.695
- What?
- No, it's impressive you know that.

18:41.871 --> 18:44.578
What were you doing in Australia?
Business or pleasure?

18:46.251 --> 18:47.866
Pleasure. You?

18:49.004 --> 18:52.622
I went down to get my sister
out of a bad relationship

18:52.716 --> 18:56.300
that, it turns out,
she didn't want to get out of.

18:56.386 --> 18:59.048
So... here I am.

19:00.557 --> 19:03.048
So, what, you were just
down under for vacation?

19:04.394 --> 19:07.557
- Actually, I went on a walkabout.
- Really?

19:08.815 --> 19:13.400
- Like... like Crocodile Dundee?
- No, not exactly.

19:13.486 --> 19:17.820
But... But it was pretty intense.
We spent ten days in the outback

19:17.907 --> 19:21.195
in nothing but our packs and our knives.

19:21.286 --> 19:24.028
We slept under the stars
and made our own fires,

19:24.122 --> 19:27.239
- hunted our own food.
- Wow.

19:29.127 --> 19:31.334
I wouldn't make it two days
without my cell phone.

19:33.923 --> 19:38.087
- You're not pulling my leg, are ya?
- Why would I pull your leg?

19:41.097 --> 19:44.715
This thing goes down,
I'm sticking with you.

20:17.675 --> 20:19.757
You can stop staring at the fire.

20:24.349 --> 20:26.055
Jacob's gone.

20:27.143 --> 20:28.883
He's gone.

20:28.978 --> 20:30.718
Why didn't he fight back?

20:33.650 --> 20:35.390
Why did he let mejust kill him?

20:35.485 --> 20:37.817
I guess he knew that he was beaten.

20:42.033 --> 20:45.491
Ben, I want you to go outside

20:45.578 --> 20:49.537
and tell Richard
that I need to talk to him.

20:50.208 --> 20:52.620
Talk to him about what?

20:54.003 --> 20:55.834
That's between me and Richard.

21:01.177 --> 21:03.668
- There's no other reason.
- That's not how it's gonna be.

21:03.763 --> 21:06.550
- You have to...
- You're not going in there.

21:06.641 --> 21:09.178
Listen to me. I already did.
Now I'm asking you to...

21:13.064 --> 21:15.680
Just back up a little. Back up.

21:18.069 --> 21:19.570
Who are they?

21:20.655 --> 21:24.398
Other than the fact that I know
they were on the Ajira flight with us,

21:25.118 --> 21:28.406
all I know is they knocked me out
and dragged my ass to some cabin,

21:28.496 --> 21:30.111
which they promptly burned, then...

21:30.874 --> 21:33.866
...brought me here
along with the dead guy in the box.

21:35.462 --> 21:37.248
They say they're the good guys.

21:41.384 --> 21:42.794
I'm not buying it either.

21:46.139 --> 21:48.471
Listen to me. Listen to me,
and listen carefully.

21:48.558 --> 21:51.265
No one goes in there
unless Jacob invites them in.

21:51.352 --> 21:54.515
Richard, that's why we're here,
because Jacob invited us.

21:54.606 --> 21:57.313
Asking me what's in the shadow of the
statue, doesn't mean you're in charge.

21:57.400 --> 21:59.982
- Then who is?
- Richard.

22:02.197 --> 22:03.733
Ben.

22:05.074 --> 22:07.816
- What happened in there?
- Everything's fine.

22:07.911 --> 22:10.243
John wants to speak to you.

22:10.330 --> 22:12.946
- ls Jacob all right?
- I'm sorry. Who are you?

22:13.041 --> 22:16.158
- Answer her question, Ben.
- Well, of course Jacob's all right.

22:16.252 --> 22:20.120
They're both together inside.
John just wants to talk to you.

22:20.548 --> 22:22.539
- John wants to talk to me?
- That's right.

22:24.761 --> 22:26.672
What are you doing?
I don't understand.

22:26.763 --> 22:28.594
I'm happy to talk to John.

22:28.681 --> 22:31.593
But, before I do, maybe you
should talk to him first.

22:53.581 --> 22:55.958
Hang on, Juliet! We're coming!

23:04.842 --> 23:06.628
Jin. Flashlight.

23:11.558 --> 23:13.844
If we could move this beam,
I think I can get down there!

23:28.866 --> 23:32.154
Too heavy. We need
something to pull it. Jin!

23:33.371 --> 23:35.578
The van!
There's chains in it. Go get 'em!

23:45.133 --> 23:46.373
Where you going, dude?

23:47.218 --> 23:48.594
And what are you doing here?

23:49.178 --> 23:53.171
I mean, I meet you in a taxi,
you know everything about me,

23:53.266 --> 23:55.552
you give me a plane ticket,
which just so happens

23:55.643 --> 23:58.806
to get me back on this island.
How'd you know that was gonna happen?

24:01.190 --> 24:02.805
Hello!

24:06.112 --> 24:08.694
Can you hear me? Why aren't
you answering my questions?

24:10.366 --> 24:12.948
My friend Jin's gonna be here
any second, so stop ignoring me...

24:13.036 --> 24:14.822
Your friend Jin won't be able to see me.

24:14.912 --> 24:18.780
- Why not?
- Because I died an hour ago.

24:21.002 --> 24:24.620
- Sorry, dude. That sucks.
- Thanks.

24:25.214 --> 24:26.545
How'd you die?

24:27.550 --> 24:30.462
l was killed by an old friend
who grew tired of my company.

24:36.059 --> 24:37.924
You want me to do
something crazy again?

24:38.019 --> 24:41.432
No. I need you to save Sayid, Hugo.

24:42.732 --> 24:45.189
- That's why Jin went to get Jack...
- Jin can't help him.

24:45.276 --> 24:48.109
You need to take Sayid to the Temple.

24:48.196 --> 24:50.107
That's the only chance he's got.

24:50.198 --> 24:52.109
And the rest of them will be safe there.

24:52.200 --> 24:54.532
The Temple?
I'm supposed to know what that is?

24:54.619 --> 24:55.825
Jin knows.

24:55.912 --> 24:59.825
Tell him to take you to the hole in the
wall where he was with the French team.

24:59.916 --> 25:02.908
Through that opening,
you can get into the Temple.

25:03.586 --> 25:05.918
You still have
that guitar case I gave you?

25:07.048 --> 25:09.039
- Yeah.
- Bring it.

25:11.135 --> 25:12.750
Who are you, dude?

25:14.347 --> 25:15.553
l'm Jacob.

25:22.146 --> 25:26.014
Hurley! Help me with Sayid.

25:26.109 --> 25:28.771
We have to get him into the van.
Juliet needs our help.

25:29.862 --> 25:30.897
Come on! We have to go!

25:42.417 --> 25:45.784
Jin, if! asked you to take me to
where there's, like, a hole in the wall,

25:45.878 --> 25:49.166
where you went with the French team,
would you know what I was talking about?

25:51.259 --> 25:53.375
- Yes.
- Good.

26:04.355 --> 26:06.220
I'll get the chain.

26:08.985 --> 26:10.145
Juliet?

26:11.487 --> 26:14.445
Stop it. Stop, Sawyer.
The van is here. The chains are coming.

26:23.499 --> 26:25.160
She ain't making any more noises.

26:25.251 --> 26:27.913
She knows we're here.
She's probably just resting.

26:28.004 --> 26:29.585
Juliet!

26:36.596 --> 26:38.461
If she dies, I'll kill him.

26:45.938 --> 26:48.099
Ladies and gentlemen,
nothing to be alarmed about,

26:48.191 --> 26:51.524
but if there is a doctor on board,
would you please press your call button?

26:55.239 --> 26:56.490
Sir, you're a doctor?

26:56.574 --> 26:58.565
- Yes.
- Could you come with me, please?

26:59.494 --> 27:03.203
We appreciate your help. A passenger
went into the restroom half an hour ago,

27:03.289 --> 27:05.154
and he's not responding when we knock.

27:06.250 --> 27:07.501
This man's a doctor.

27:07.585 --> 27:11.123
- If he's unconscious in there...
- The lock. lt's jammed or something.

27:11.214 --> 27:12.545
Can I be of assistance?

27:13.716 --> 27:14.831
Excuse me.

27:27.688 --> 27:29.098
He's not breathing.

27:38.241 --> 27:39.981
What's going on back there, Earhart?

27:40.076 --> 27:42.692
Everything's fine, sir.
Please just stay in your seat.

27:42.787 --> 27:44.027
Looks peachy.

27:45.039 --> 27:46.950
- I'm gonna need your help.
- What can I do?

27:47.041 --> 27:48.201
I need you...

27:49.544 --> 27:51.910
Hold this over his nose and mouth.
Hold it there,

27:52.004 --> 27:54.495
- and do not let any air escape.
- OK. Now?

27:54.590 --> 27:55.875
Yes, now.

28:00.930 --> 28:02.841
Something's blocking his air passage.

28:09.564 --> 28:12.271
We have to open it up. I need
something sharp... A razor.

28:14.485 --> 28:16.146
- I got a
_ pen.
A pen?

28:16.237 --> 28:18.569
lt's regulations.
There's nothing sharp.

28:18.656 --> 28:20.692
A pen! Just a pen.

28:20.783 --> 28:22.739
I had a pen in my jacket, but it's gone.

28:23.619 --> 28:24.904
Damn it.

28:30.877 --> 28:32.162
I got it. I got it.

28:41.888 --> 28:44.630
Relax. Just relax. Breathe.

28:49.937 --> 28:50.926
Am I alive?

28:52.481 --> 28:53.982
Yeah. Yeah, you're alive.

28:57.445 --> 28:58.560
Terrific.

29:14.003 --> 29:17.336
- You got it?
- OK, Jin! We're good down here!

29:20.760 --> 29:22.250
Hit it!

29:35.149 --> 29:36.764
Give me the flashlight.

29:56.462 --> 29:57.577
Juliet.

30:05.304 --> 30:07.135
OK. All right.

30:07.223 --> 30:09.054
Juliet. Come here.

30:12.645 --> 30:13.885
Juliet?

30:14.563 --> 30:16.474
Hey, hey, hey.

30:16.565 --> 30:19.352
I'm here. Come on, baby.
Hey, come on, wake up.

30:19.443 --> 30:21.104
Wake up.

30:25.908 --> 30:26.897
Hi.

30:28.411 --> 30:29.947
Hey.

30:34.625 --> 30:37.287
Where... Where are we?

30:37.378 --> 30:40.711
Don't worry about that. You're fine.

30:40.798 --> 30:42.754
I gotta get you out of here, OK?

30:47.972 --> 30:50.054
It didn't work.

30:51.350 --> 30:52.590
We're still on the island.

30:53.602 --> 30:55.854
It's OK. It's OK.

30:55.938 --> 30:58.645
