You couldn't kill him yourself,
so you made me do it.

1:13:39.749 --> 1:13:42.786
I didn't make you do anything.

1:13:46.464 --> 1:13:47.749
You should know...

1:13:49.467 --> 1:13:51.719
...he was very confused
when you killed him.

1:13:51.803 --> 1:13:54.761
I seriously doubt
that Jacob was ever confused.

1:13:54.848 --> 1:13:56.839
I'm not talking about Jacob.

1:13:59.185 --> 1:14:01.267
I'm talking about John Locke.

1:14:03.648 --> 1:14:06.606
Do you wanna know
what he was thinking while you...

1:14:07.736 --> 1:14:10.148
...choked the life out of him, Benjamin?

1:14:10.238 --> 1:14:13.025
What the last thought
that ran through his head was?

1:14:14.534 --> 1:14:16.490
"I don't understand."

1:14:20.582 --> 1:14:23.289
Isn't that just the
saddest thing you ever heard?

1:14:26.004 --> 1:14:27.540
But it's fitting, in a way.

1:14:28.590 --> 1:14:33.459
Because when John first came
to the island, he was a very sad man.

1:14:34.137 --> 1:14:39.222
A victim shouting at the world
for being told what he couldn't do,

1:14:39.309 --> 1:14:40.799
even though they were right.

1:14:42.228 --> 1:14:47.564
He was weak and pathetic
and irreparably broken.

1:14:49.402 --> 1:14:54.863
But, despite all that, there was
something admirable about him.

1:14:54.949 --> 1:14:59.067
He was the only one of them
who didn't want to leave.

1:14:59.162 --> 1:15:01.244
The only one who realized

1:15:01.331 --> 1:15:06.371
how pitiful the life
he'd left behind actually was.

1:15:15.929 --> 1:15:17.715
What do you want?

1:15:19.265 --> 1:15:21.972
Well, that's the great irony here,
Ben, because...

1:15:22.936 --> 1:15:25.643
...I want the one thing
that John Locke didn't.

1:15:28.566 --> 1:15:31.774
I want to go home.

1:15:44.332 --> 1:15:45.993
Good-bye, dude.

1:15:47.001 --> 1:15:52.086
If you ever wanna talk, I'm around.

1:16:01.766 --> 1:16:02.755
What?

1:16:05.729 --> 1:16:07.139
Nothing.

1:16:21.911 --> 1:16:22.900
Hey.

1:16:25.999 --> 1:16:27.079
Where are we?

1:16:29.169 --> 1:16:33.663
- We're in a temple.
- We got caught by the Others again?

1:16:34.090 --> 1:16:39.881
Yeah. Only this time,
they're protecting us. I think.

1:16:41.973 --> 1:16:45.010
- Of course they are.
- You all right?

1:16:52.192 --> 1:16:53.978
I'm so sorry.

1:17:09.417 --> 1:17:11.658
You know what you said
back at the hatch?

1:17:12.587 --> 1:17:14.418
He's just trying to help us.

1:17:16.341 --> 1:17:18.297
I ain't gonna kill Jack.

1:17:21.805 --> 1:17:25.389
He deserves to suffer on this rock
just like the rest of us.

1:17:30.271 --> 1:17:32.432
Yeah.

1:17:32.524 --> 1:17:35.732
I know, and... Do you think
I knew this was gonna happen?

1:17:36.945 --> 1:17:40.187
l scheduled it so soon
because I want to get it over with.

1:17:43.034 --> 1:17:46.367
I don't know, Mom. He's not here,
so I can't tell you what to tell them,

1:17:46.454 --> 1:17:48.866
other then we can't
have the service without him.

1:17:50.250 --> 1:17:51.410
Yeah.

1:17:52.335 --> 1:17:54.451
I will call you if! hear anything.

1:17:57.549 --> 1:17:59.130
What did you lose?

1:18:00.510 --> 1:18:01.795
Excuse me?

1:18:01.886 --> 1:18:05.094
They lost one of my bags.
What about you?

1:18:07.225 --> 1:18:09.056
You wouldn't believe me if I told you.

1:18:10.061 --> 1:18:11.676
Try me.

1:18:12.689 --> 1:18:14.429
They lost my father.

1:18:16.276 --> 1:18:17.607
I'm sorry?

1:18:17.694 --> 1:18:22.529
He died in Australia a couple days ago,
and I flew down to get him.

1:18:27.620 --> 1:18:29.406
My condolences.

1:18:30.832 --> 1:18:34.165
The coffin was supposed to go
on the plane in Sydney, but it didn't.

1:18:34.711 --> 1:18:37.373
He's somewhere in transit,
which is their way of saying

1:18:37.463 --> 1:18:39.670
they have no idea where the hell he is.

1:18:40.466 --> 1:18:42.252
Well, how could they know?

1:18:43.970 --> 1:18:47.428
They checked him in. They've gotta
have some kind of tracking system.

1:18:47.515 --> 1:18:51.258
No, I'm not talking about the coffin.
How could they know where he is?

1:18:53.730 --> 1:18:57.973
They didn't lose your father.
They just lost his body.

1:19:09.996 --> 1:19:12.783
Either way, your story
beats the hell out of mine.

1:19:12.874 --> 1:19:16.241
All that was in my suitcase
was a bunch of knives. Thanks.

1:19:16.336 --> 1:19:20.295
- You some kind of salesman?
- Yeah, somethin' like that.

1:19:22.884 --> 1:19:26.593
Well, it's nice talking to you.
I hope you find that coffin.

1:19:28.514 --> 1:19:30.766
- I hope you find your knives.
- Yeah, thanks.

1:19:31.351 --> 1:19:33.216
Mind if I ask what happened to you?

1:19:35.229 --> 1:19:38.767
I'm sorry. I'm only asking
because I'm a spinal surgeon.

1:19:38.858 --> 1:19:41.099
- I didn't mean to...
- Oh, no. Don't worry about it.

1:19:42.528 --> 1:19:44.610
Surgery isn't gonna
do anything to help me.

1:19:44.697 --> 1:19:46.528
My condition is irreversible.

1:19:47.909 --> 1:19:49.365
Nothing's irreversible.

1:19:59.003 --> 1:20:03.838
If you ever want a consult...
just give me a call.

1:20:05.760 --> 1:20:07.216
It's on the house.

1:20:08.221 --> 1:20:10.177
Well, thanks.

1:20:11.849 --> 1:20:15.262
"Jack Shephard."
l'm John. John Locke.

1:20:16.729 --> 1:20:19.562
- It's nice to meet you, John.
- Nice to meet you, too.

1:20:23.695 --> 1:20:25.185
- Thanks.
- You're welcome.

1:20:34.998 --> 1:20:36.579
What the hell is that?

1:20:59.439 --> 1:21:00.804
Don't shoot him! Don't shoot him!

1:21:03.735 --> 1:21:07.944
l'm seein' it,
but I'm still not believin' it.

1:21:12.535 --> 1:21:13.945
Hello, Richard.

1:21:15.288 --> 1:21:18.075
It's good to see you
out of those chains.

1:21:23.713 --> 1:21:25.669
- You?
- Me.

1:21:39.270 --> 1:21:43.639
I am very disappointed... in all of you.

1:22:28.027 --> 1:22:30.359
- You're Shephard?
- Yeah.

1:22:30.446 --> 1:22:32.152
We need to speak to you privately.

1:22:35.284 --> 1:22:37.616
If you've got something
to say to me, then say it.

1:22:37.703 --> 1:22:40.319
OthenNise, just leave me alone.

1:22:40.414 --> 1:22:43.952
I don't think you're understanding
me here. I'm asking politely.

1:22:44.836 --> 1:22:49.250
You either get up and come with us on
your own, or I'll have you dragged out.

1:22:51.884 --> 1:22:54.876
- and it's not going to be here.
- Is that right?

1:23:03.563 --> 1:23:04.973
Jack!

1:23:06.023 --> 1:23:07.433
Oh, my God.

1:23:18.744 --> 1:23:20.405
What happened?
